e lack of the promised immersion, until the brain-computer interface is finally finished.										</li>									</ol>								</li>								<li>									In <a href="2">Part 2</a>,									the virtual reality platform called Virtuality and its flagship world called the Sphidiverse becomes fully operational, while Tom and Xiu continue to explore it.									<ol>										<li>											In <a href="2/1">Episode 1</a>,											Tom and Xiu both finally experience the fully immersive virtual world that promises to relieve them of their respective major life problems.										</li>										<li>											In <a href="2/2">Episode 2</a>,											Tom undergoes a traumatic experience in the virtual world that demonstrates that the full immersiveness it offers can be as painful as it is pleasurable.										</li>										<li>											In <a href="2/3">Episode 3</a>,											both the users of Virtuality and the system itself adapt to help everyone avoid unpleasantness like that that Tom has recently experienced.										</li>									</ol>								</li>								<li>									In <a href="3">Part 3</a>,									mind-uploaded Xiuying adjusts to her new "afterlife", the virtual world goes public, and the true motives behind the construction of the virtual world are revealed.									<ol>										<li>											In <a href="3/1">Episode 1</a>,											Xiuying becomes one of the first mind-uploaded users of Virtuality, and suffers something of an existential crisis on the process thereof.										</li>										<li>											In <a href="3/2">Episode 2</a>,											Virtuality becomes available to the public, society adapts to its existence, and one secret purpose of it is brought to fruition.										</li>										<li>											In <a href="3/3">Episode 3</a>,											the darker secret purpose behind Virtuality's creation becomes apparent, as the immortal Xio behind it all offloads the mind of his mad dead lover into the virtual world.										</li>									</ol>								</li>							</ol>						</li>					</ol>				</section>					<? require $_SERVER['DOCUMENT_ROOT'] . "/includes/footer-global.php" ?>